预设变量
${userHome} - 用户主文件夹路径
${workspaceFolder} - the path of the folder opened in VS Code 在VS Code中打开的文件夹路径
${workspaceFolderBasename} - the name of the folder opened in VS Code without any slashes (/) 在VS Code中打开的文件夹名称，不带任何斜杠（/）
${file} - the current opened file 当前打开的文件
${fileWorkspaceFolder} - the current opened file's workspace folder 当前打开的文件的工作空间文件夹
${relativeFile} - the current opened file relative to workspaceFolder -当前打开的文件相对于工作区文件夹
${relativeFileDirname} - the current opened file's dirname relative to workspaceFolder 当前打开的文件相对于工作空间文件夹的目录名
${fileBasename} - the current opened file's basename 当前打开的文件的文件名
${fileBasenameNoExtension} - the current opened file's basename with no file extension 当前打开的文件的基本名称，没有文件扩展名
${fileExtname} - the current opened file's extension -当前打开文件的扩展名
${fileDirname} - the current opened file's folder path 当前打开的文件的文件夹路径
${fileDirnameBasename} - the current opened file's folder name 当前打开的文件的文件夹名称
${cwd} - the task runner's current working directory upon the startup of VS Code 任务运行器在Vs Code启动时的当前工作目录
${lineNumber} - the current selected line number in the active file 活动文件中当前选定的行号
${selectedText} - the current selected text in the active file 活动文件中当前选定的文本
${execPath} - the path to the running VS Code executable 运行中的VS Code可执行文件的路径运行中的VS Code可执行文件的路径
${defaultBuildTask} - the name of the default build task 默认生成任务的名称
${pathSeparator} - the character used by the operating system to separate components in file paths 操作系统在文件路径中用来分隔组件的字符
${/} - shorthand for ${pathSeparator} ${pathSeparator}的简写

预定义变量应用示例
A file located at /home/your-username/your-project/folder/file.ext opened in your editor;
The directory /home/your-username/your-project opened as your root workspace.
So you will have the following values for each variable:
${userHome} - /home/your-username
${workspaceFolder} - /home/your-username/your-project
${workspaceFolderBasename} - your-project
${file} - /home/your-username/your-project/folder/file.ext
${fileWorkspaceFolder} - /home/your-username/your-project
${relativeFile} - folder/file.ext
${relativeFileDirname} - folder
${fileBasename} - file.ext
${fileBasenameNoExtension} - file
${fileDirname} - /home/your-username/your-project/folder
${fileExtname} - .ext
${lineNumber} - line number of the cursor
${selectedText} - text selected in your code editor
${execPath} - location of Code.exe
${pathSeparator} - / on macOS or linux, \ on Windows
